         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/5/86 ¶  ¶ It was my intention, dear Mr Blackett, to call on you ere this; but the work in the Department is still so overwhelming, that I can not get away even in evening-hours or on Sundays. ¶  ¶ ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.05.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Cuthbert Blackett</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/5/86</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It was my intention, dear Mr Blackett, to call on you ere this; but the work in the Department is still so overwhelming, that I can not get away even in evening-hours or on Sundays.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I went however to Dr Springthorpe, and we discussed the intended experiments, for which you will give aid, and in which you will share, at length. The first plant, to be delt<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">dealt?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> with, shall be <name key="Gratiola%20Peruviana">Gratiola Peruviana</name>; it will be gathered in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">considerable quantity within</hi>
               </seg> the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">next</hi>
               </seg> days. The continental physicians use the stiff extract, reduced from the strained decoction by gentle evaporation, finally in the hot water bath. So perhaps you will kindly arrange the preliminaries, as the herb would suffer, had it to lay bye. I would also advise, that some Gratiolin according to Wittsteins direction (see my edition)<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Wittstein (1878), i.e. B78.06.09, p. 96.</p>
               </note> be prepared</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I really must try, to get over to you some evening soon; but the Plants of Capt Everills New Guinean Expedition<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">New Guinea exploring expedition, 1885.</p>
               </note> take up much time, and I am not at all far on with the "Key," part I. (II is doing.)<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Part II of M's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Key</seg> (B86.04.05) was being issued; Part I (B88.11.02) was not published for another two years.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Gratiola%20Peruviana">Gratiola Peruviana</name>
            </p>
